import React from "react";

class ProductList extends React.Component {
    constructor(props) {
        super(props);
        this.state = {
            product: {
                SNO: '110ab',
                IMAGE: "https://www.flipkart.com/hmtr-black-day-date-working-analog-watch-men/p/itm871afffe0c762?pid=WATG5YMHYJZBRGYG&lid=LSTWATG5YMHYJZBRGYGZAUBN8&marketplace=FLIPKART&store=r18&srno=b_1_1&otracker=browse&fm=organic&iid=en_ci_P0c5pcOMydve2fJaJRHV6Uzr3K8ny4hlTjsUDGd7lL1JtYLwClhwe7zRo7gf5nAxdvyoREVW73-xKZsUqnQ%3D%3D&ppt=None&ppn=None&ssid=7k7qwf88ls0000001697804467447",
                NAME: 'watch',
                PRICE: 2000,
                QRY: 2,
                TOTAL: ""
            }

        }
    }

    render() {
        return ( <
            React.Fragment >
            <
            h1 className = "head " > Product - List < /h1>  <
            section className = "p-3" >
            <
            div class = "container" >
            <
            div class = "row" >
            <
            div class = "col" >
            <
            p class = "h3 text-primary" > Cart Items <
            /p>  <
            p className = "lead" > Radom Word Generator tool to generate random words from a list of commonly used words.Generate up to 50 random words at a time. < /p> < /
            div > <
            /div> < /
            div >
            <
            /section>   <
            section className = "container-1 text-center" >
            <
            div className = "row row align-items-start" >
            <
            div className = "col" >
            <
            table className = "table table-hover text-center text-striped" >

            <
            thead className = "bg-danger " >
            <
            tr >
            <
            th > SNO: < /th> <
            th > IMAGE: < /th> <
            th > NAME: < /th> <
            th > PRICE: < /th> <
            th > QTY: < /th> <
            th > TOTAL: < /th> < /
            tr >
            <
            /thead>  <
            tbody className = "bd-primary text-white" >
            <
            tr >
            <
            td > { this.state.product.sno } < /td>  <
            td >
            <
            img src = { this.state.product.image }
            width = "50"
            height = "50"
            alt = "" / >

            <
            /td> < /
            tr >

            <
            /tbody>


            <
            /
            table > < /
            div > <
            /div> < /
            section > <
            /
            React.Fragment >
        );
    }
}

export default ProductList;
